replies.bodyText:
Guava is a very popular Java library (from Google) that provides a lot of handy and convenient utilities, annotations, and language idioms. In this case, if jib-build-plan depended on Guava, we would have been able to use the Preconditions class from Guava.
Preconditions.checkArgument(!platforms.isEmpty(), "platforms set cannot be empty");
However, since we want jib-build-plan to be as much lightweight as possible, we don't use Guava. (jib-core uses Guava, OTOH.)
